3 WHEREAS, The American braille tactile flag was created by the Kansas Braille
4 Transcription Institute in Wichita, Kansas, to allow blind Americans and blind veterans to
5 experience the American flag; and
6 WHEREAS, Maryland has five State veterans’ cemeteries visited by thousands of
7 people annually; and
8 WHEREAS, The State of Maryland is known as a state that recognizes the great
9 contributions of our blind community and honors the dedication of our uniformed services
10 members and veterans; now, therefore,
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – State Government
14 9–906.
15 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
16 (2) “AMERICAN BRAILLE TACTILE FLAG” MEANS A TACTILE FLAG
17 DESIGNED TO ALLOW BLIND PEOPLE TO EXPERIENCE THE AMERICAN FLAG,
18 INCLUDING A FLAG CREATED BY THE KANSAS BRAILLE TRANSCRIPTION INSTITUTE.
19 (3) “Eligible dependent” means:
20 (i) a child who meets the requirements stated in 38 C.F.R. §
21 38.620(e); or
22 (ii) a parent who meets the requirements stated in 38 C.F.R. §
23 38.620(i).
24 [(3)] (4) “Eligible spouse” means a spouse who meets the requirements
25 stated in 38 C.F.R. § 38.620(e).
26 [(4)] (5) “State veterans’ cemetery” means a cemetery that the
27 Department establishes under this section.
28 [(5)] (6) In this section and in § 9–907 of this subtitle, “veteran” means
29 an individual who:
30 (i) served other than dishonorably on active duty in the armed
31 forces of the United States; or

