4 [(6)] (7) “Washington Cemetery” means the Civil War cemetery grounds
5 authorized by Chapter 213 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 1870.
6 (b) The Department may establish one or more cemeteries in the State for the
7 burial of veterans and their eligible spouse or dependents as authorized by the Secretary.
8 (J) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DESIGNATE A LOCATION FOR AN AMERICAN
9 BRAILLE TACTILE FLAG TO BE PLACED IN ONE OR MORE STATE VETERANS’
10 CEMETERIES AS AUTHORIZED BY THE SECRETARY TO HONOR MEMBERS OF THE
11 UNIFORMED SERVICES, VETERANS, AND OTHER INDIVIDUALS IN THE STATE WHO
12 ARE BLIND OR VISUALLY IMPAIRED.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
14 October 1, 2025.

